    <dl>
        <dt><strong>Electric Vehicles</strong></dt>
        <dd>Electric vehicles (EVs) are transforming the transportation landscape by offering a cleaner, more
            sustainable
            alternative to traditional gasoline-powered cars. As global concern over climate change grows, EVs have
            become a key
            focus for reducing carbon emissions. According to the<mark>U.S. Department of Energy</mark> , EVs produce
            fewer emissions and can be powered by renewable energy sources. Meanwhile, companies like <mark>Tesla</mark>
            and Rivian are innovating rapidly in this space.
        </dd>
    </dl> 
        <ul>
        <h2>Advantages</h2>
            <li><mark>Environmental Benefits:</mark> Zero tailpipe emissions</li>
            <li><mark>Lower Operating Costs:</mark>Less maintenance, cheaper charging vs fuel</li>
            <li><mark>Government Incentives:</mark>Tax credits and rebates available in many regions</li>
        </ul>
